== NAME

yapet_colors - format of YAPET color configuration


== DESCRIPTION

The color scheme of YAPET can be customized by setting the _colors_
option in {rcfile}. It has the following syntax:

```
_colors_=_OBJ1_:_<fg1>__<bg1>__<attr1>_;...;_OBJN_:_<fgN>__<bgN>__<attrN>_
```

_OBJN_:: The UI object for which the color is set. See <xref linkend="tab.uiobjects" /> for possible values.
_<fgN>_:: The foreground color of the UI object. See <xref linkend="tab.colors"/> for possible values.

      <varlistentry>
	<term>_<bgN>_</term>
	<listitem>
	  <para>
	    The background color of the UI object. See <xref
	    linkend="tab.colors"/> for possible values.
	  </para>
	</listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
	<term>_<attrN>_</term>
	<listitem>
	  <para>
	    The attribute of the UI object. Attributes are used if the
	    terminal does not support colors. See <xref
	    linkend="tab.attributes"/> for possible values.
	  </para>
	</listitem>
      </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>

